            <commentid>33854</commentid>
            <who name="Christopher Zuendorf">christopher.zuendorf</who>
            <bug_when>2013-09-09 15:21:26 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>The window scrollPosition is set to a wrong position on orientationChange.

Explicit setting window.scrollTo(0,0) on orientationChange solves one part of the problem.
Additionally the document.clientHeight is not equal to window.innerHeight, which causes the overlay of the Tabbar in front of the page.

document.documentElement.style.height = window.innerHeight + &quot;px&quot;;

solves the problem on orientationChange event, too.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
